                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14048679" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 1 Jul 2014 09:28:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch to fix (along with a unit test). The changes in &lt;tt&gt;Message.java&lt;/tt&gt; is because currently the NPE is thrown during message encoding, which somehow ended up not being caught properly: the result is that as of now, the code of the description ends up with no response of the server and no message in the log whatsoever. While the patch fixes the NPE in the first place, figured extending the try/catch is not a bad idea either.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14053745" author="tjake" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 15:16:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There looks to be a bug in ProtocolEncoder.   You  release the body on any Throwable then add it to the Frame anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14053749" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 15:19:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oops, I meant to re-throw after the release. I can fix upon commit if there is nothing else, or I can re-upload a version updated with that change if you prefer.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14053751" author="tjake" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 15:21:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure fix on commit +1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14053798" author="slebresne" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2014 16:09:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commited then, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
